\cf0 When compared to mood, tense is pretty basic.  Tense tells when an action is completed: in the past, the present, or the future.  Duration is not taken into account, and as a result, there are only three tenses.  Tenses are shown through the use of suffixes.\
\
PAST\
Suffix: -l\'92go\
English examples:\
I played games.\
I used to play games.\
\
PRESENT\
Suffix: None\
English example: You listen to music.\
\
FUTURE\
Suffix: -l\'92\'e4\
English example: He will talk to us.\
