INFINITIVE\
Suffix: -l\'92gi\
Used when there are multiple verbs in a sentence, to distinguish between the action and the other verbs.\
English example: In \'93He wanted to stop\'94, \'93wanted\'94 is the action and \'93to stop\'94 is the infinitive.\
\
NEGATIVE\
Prefix: fil\'92-\
Used in combination with moods to show that an action did not take place.  The negative prefix goes before the mood prefix.  When a mood prefix exists (the mood is not indicative), remove the \'93l\'92-\'94 from the end of the negative prefix, and combine with the mood.  For example, negative alethic would have a prefix of \'93fidul\'92-\'94\
English example: I do not listen to that kind of music.\
